==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wulfenite
<hw>Wul"fen*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named after F.
X. <etsep>Wulfen</etsep>, an Australian mineralogist.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Native lead molybdate occurring in tetragonal
crystals, usually tabular, and of a bright orange-yellow to red, gray,
or brown color; -- also called <altname>yellow lead
ore</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wull</ent>⟦br⟧
